        {
          "text": "Q: Can LaylatВӯulВӯQadr (the Night of Decree) be seen with the naked eye? Some people claim that if a person sees LaylatВӯulВӯQadr, they see a light in the sky and the like. How did the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him) and the Sahabah (Companions of the Prophet (may Allah be pleased with all of them) see it? How can a person know that they have seen LaylatВӯ ulВӯQadr? Will a person still gain its reward, if they could not see that night? Please explain and mention the evidence.",
